In 2008, Holmes edited FESTSCHRIFT, with essays by Carlos Basualdo, Nicholas Baume, and James Rondeau.
Holmes has been a visiting critic for Skowhegan, Yale School of Art, Art Omi, University of Connecticut, Nova Scotia College of Art and Design, University of Lethbridge and Hartford Art School. Projects have been reviewed in The New York Times, Art in America, Art Forum, The New Yorker Magazine, artnet, artUS, Art News, Tema Celeste, Flash Art International and Art New England. He has appeared on TV and Radio in the United States and Europe to speak about contemporary art, and art and social change, including NBC Miami, BBC5 London, CBC Halifax and Toronto, and Connecticut Public Radio.
Selected publications[edit]

"Charles Ledray", Bass Museum of Art, 2013.
"I Didn’t Know They Were Canadian", in Oh Canada, MIT Press, 2012.
"Hartford Arts Hurt By Loss Of Curators" in Hartford Courant, Op Ed, September 26, 2010
